60 (κατανύσσω);","strongs_def":"a prickling (sensation, as of the limbs asleep), i.e. (by implication, (perhaps by some confusion with G3506 (νεύω) or even with G3571 (νύξ))) stupor (lethargy)","kjv_def":"slumber","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"slumber(1x)"},"G2653":{"id":"G2653","lemma":"καταναθεματίζω","translit":"katanathematízō","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) (intensive) and G332 (ἀναθεματίζω);","strongs_def":"to imprecate","kjv_def":"curse","pos":"verb","usage":"curse(1x)"},"G2611":{"id":"G2611","lemma":"καταδέω","translit":"katadéō","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and G1210 (δέω);","strongs_def":"to tie down, i.e. bandage (a wound)","kjv_def":"bind up","pos":"verb"},"G2690":{"id":"G2690","lemma":"καταστρέφω","translit":"katastréphō","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and G4762 (στρέφω);","strongs_def":"to turn upside down, i.e. upset","kjv_def":"overthrow","pos":"verb","usage":"overthrow(2x)"},"G2624":{"id":"G2624","lemma":"κατακληροδοτέω","translit":"kataklērodotéō","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and a derivative of a compound of G2819 (κλῆρος) and G1325 (δίδωμι);","strongs_def":"to be a giver of lots to each, i.e. (by implication) to apportion an estate","kjv_def":"divide by lot","pos":"verb"},"G2670":{"id":"G2670","lemma":"καταποντίζω","translit":"katapontízō","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and a derivative of the same as G4195 (Πόντος);","strongs_def":"to plunge down, i.e. submerge","kjv_def":"drown, sink","pos":"verb","usage":"sink(1x), drown(1x)"},"G2664":{"id":"G2664","lemma":"καταπαύω","translit":"katapaúō","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and G3973 (παύω);","strongs_def":"to settle down, i.e. (literally) to colonize, or (figuratively) to (cause to) desist","kjv_def":"cease, (give) rest(-rain)","pos":"verb","usage":"restrain(1x), rest(1x), cease(1x)"},"G2682":{"id":"G2682","lemma":"κατασκήνωσις","translit":"kataskḗnōsis","derivation":"from G2681 (κατασκηνόω);","strongs_def":"an encamping, i.e. (figuratively) a perch","kjv_def":"nest","pos":"neuter noun","usage":"nest(2x)"},"G2692":{"id":"G2692","lemma":"καταστροφή","translit":"katastrophḗ","derivation":"from G2690 (καταστρέφω);","strongs_def":"an overturn (\"catastrophe\"), i.e. demolition; figuratively, apostasy","kjv_def":"overthrow, subverting"},"G2698":{"id":"G2698","lemma":"κατατίθημι","translit":"katatíthēmi","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and G5087 (τίθημι);","strongs_def":"to place down, i.e. deposit (literally or figuratively)","kjv_def":"do, lay, shew","pos":"verb","usage":"lay(1x), show(1x), do(1x)"},"G2643":{"id":"G2643","lemma":"καταλλαγή","translit":"katallagḗ","derivation":"from G2644 (καταλλάσσω);","strongs_def":"exchange (figuratively, adjustment), i.e. restoration to (the divine) favor","kjv_def":"atonement, reconciliation(-ing)","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"reconciliation(2x), atonement(1x), reconciling(1x)"},"G2667":{"id":"G2667","lemma":"καταπίπτω","translit":"katapíptō","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and G4098 (πίπτω);","strongs_def":"to fall down","kjv_def":"fall (down)","pos":"verb","usage":"fall(1x)"},"G2621":{"id":"G2621","lemma":"κατάκειμαι","translit":"katákeimai","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and G2749 (κεῖμαι);","strongs_def":"to lie down, i.e. (by implication) be sick; specially, to recline at a meal","kjv_def":"keep, lie, sit at meat (down)","pos":"verb","usage":"lie(6x), keep(1x)"},"G2687":{"id":"G2687","lemma":"καταστέλλω","translit":"katastéllō","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and G4724 (στέλλω);","strongs_def":"to put down, i.e. quell","kjv_def":"appease, quiet","pos":"verb","usage":"appease(1x), quiet(1x)"},"G2649":{"id":"G2649","lemma":"καταμαρτυρέω","translit":"katamartyréō","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and G3140 (μαρτυρέω);","strongs_def":"to testify against","kjv_def":"witness against","pos":"verb"},"G2654":{"id":"G2654","lemma":"καταναλίσκω","translit":"katanalískō","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and G355 (ἀναλίσκω);","strongs_def":"to consume utterly","kjv_def":"consume","pos":"verb","usage":"consume(1x)"},"G269