":"κατασείω","translit":"kataseíō","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and G4579 (σείω);","strongs_def":"to sway downward, i.e. make a signal","kjv_def":"beckon","pos":"verb","usage":"beckon(4x)"},"G2699":{"id":"G2699","lemma":"κατατομή","translit":"katatomḗ","derivation":"from a compound of G2596 (κατά) and (to cut);","strongs_def":"a cutting down (off), i.e. mutilation (ironically)","kjv_def":"concision"},"G2630":{"id":"G2630","lemma":"κατακρημνίζω","translit":"katakrēmnízō","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and a derivative of G2911 (κρημνός);","strongs_def":"to precipitate down","kjv_def":"cast down headlong","pos":"verb"},"G2671":{"id":"G2671","lemma":"κατάρα","translit":"katára","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) (intensive) and G685 (ἀρά);","strongs_def":"imprecation, execration","kjv_def":"curse(-d, ing)","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"curse(3x), cursing(2x), cursed(1x)"},"G2689":{"id":"G2689","lemma":"καταστολή","translit":"katastolḗ","derivation":"from G2687 (καταστέλλω);","strongs_def":"a deposit, i.e. (specially) costume","kjv_def":"apparel"},"G2619":{"id":"G2619","lemma":"κατακαλύπτω","translit":"katakalýptō","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and G2572 (καλύπτω);","strongs_def":"to cover wholly, i.e. veil","kjv_def":"cover, hide"},"G2608":{"id":"G2608","lemma":"κατάγνυμι","translit":"katágnymi","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and the base of G4486 (ῥήγνυμι);","strongs_def":"to rend in pieces, i.e. crack apart","kjv_def":"break","pos":"verb","usage":"break(4x)"},"G2666":{"id":"G2666","lemma":"καταπίνω","translit":"katapínō","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and G4095 (πίνω);","strongs_def":"to drink down, i.e. gulp entire (literally or figuratively)","kjv_def":"devour, drown, swallow (up)","pos":"verb","usage":"swallow(4x), swallow(1x), drown(1x), devour(1x)"},"G2677":{"id":"G2677","lemma":"καταρτισμός","translit":"katartismós","derivation":"from G2675 (καταρτίζω);","strongs_def":"complete furnishing (objectively)","kjv_def":"perfecting","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"perfecting(1x)"},"G2625":{"id":"G2625","lemma":"κατακλίνω","translit":"kataklínō","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and G2827 (κλίνω);","strongs_def":"to recline down, i.e. (specially) to take a place at table","kjv_def":"(make) sit down (at meat)","pos":"verb"},"G2603":{"id":"G2603","lemma":"καταβραβεύω","translit":"katabrabeúō","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and G1018 (βραβεύω) (in its original sense);","strongs_def":"to award the price against, i.e. (figuratively) to defraud (of salvation)","kjv_def":"beguile of reward","pos":"verb"},"G2614":{"id":"G2614","lemma":"καταδιώκω","translit":"katadiṓkō","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and G1377 (διώκω);","strongs_def":"to hunt down, i.e. search for","kjv_def":"follow after","pos":"verb"},"G2607":{"id":"G2607","lemma":"καταγινώσκω","translit":"kataginṓskō","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and G1097 (γινώσκω);","strongs_def":"to note against, i.e. find fault with","kjv_def":"blame, condemn"},"G2655":{"id":"G2655","lemma":"καταναρκάω","translit":"katanarkáō","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and (to be numb);","strongs_def":"to grow utterly torpid, i.e. (by implication) slothful (figuratively, expensive)","kjv_def":"be burdensome (chargeable)"},"G2612":{"id":"G2612","lemma":"κατάδηλος","translit":"katádēlos","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) intensive and G1212 (δῆλος);","strongs_def":"manifest","kjv_def":"far more evident","pos":"adjective","usage":"evident(1x)"},"G2616":{"id":"G2616","lemma":"καταδυναστεύω","translit":"katadynasteúō","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and a derivative of G1413 (δυνάστης);","strongs_def":"to exercise dominion against, i.e. oppress","kjv_def":"oppress","pos":"verb","usage":"oppress(2x)"},"G2632":{"id":"G2632","lemma":"κατακρίνω","translit":"katakrínō","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and G2919 (κρίνω);","strongs_def":"to judge against, i.e. sentence","kjv_def":"condemn, damn","pos":"verb","usage":"condemn(17x), damn(2x)"},"G2688":{"id":"G2688","lemma":"κατάστημα","translit":"katástēma","derivati